patient_dialogue: wer: This is Participant 1002.  Uhm.. the date is February 19th, 2019, and this is Scene 2.
interviewer_dialogue: Hi.  This is Interviewer, the landlady.

patient_dialogue: Aw, yes.  I’m tryin’ to see what’s goin’ on with my ceilin’.  It’s leakin’ and I told you about it before and you haven’t fixed it yet, and I’m tryin’ to see what can you do about it so my stuff don’t get wet.
interviewer_dialogue: I’m sorry.  I haven’t had enough time to get over to fix it, but I’ve been very busy.

patient_dialogue: Well, you need to come on and do it, ‘cause it’s rainin’ and my stuff ‘bout to get wet.  ‘Less you gonna buy me some new stuff.
interviewer_dialogue: Uhm.. I have a list and you’re on the list, but there are other problems that are more serious.

patient_dialogue: Okay.  Serious?  Uh.. I need you to send a maintenance man or somebody over here to fix this. <coughs> Today.
interviewer_dialogue: It didn’t sound that bad the last time you called.

patient_dialogue: I was bein’ nice and now it’s- now it’s really cutting up [ph?] and leakin’ in on my stuff, and I need you to fix it.
interviewer_dialogue: Uhm.. so what have you done about the problem so far?

patient_dialogue: I’ve waited on you.  What can I do?  Put out some pans to catch the water.
interviewer_dialogue: Well, I have a lot of other tenants with problems that are ahead of yours.

patient_dialogue: Uh.. tell you what, if y’all don’t fix it, I’ll call the city on you.  I’m i-- not in a livable apartment.  Unless you either fix it or move me to another apartment.
interviewer_dialogue: Yeah, that sounds serious.  I’ll be uh.. right over.
